    "finalText": "I hit a directory lookup issue on Westfield — the project team query failed because the people/company relationship in the data is ambiguous.\n\nWhat I can tell you from the current Westfield intelligence packet is this:\n\n- **Andrew Cannon** — clearly acting as **Assistant Project Manager** on Westfield  \n  - Shown in email signature: “Assistant Project Manager at Alleato Group”\n- **Brandon Clymer** — involved at **executive / company leadership** level  \n  - Shown in email signature: “CEO at Alleato Group”\n- **Jesse Dawson** — on the email chain, but **role not confirmed** from the data I have\n- **Douglas Franklin** — on the email chain, but **role not confirmed**\n- **Mike Ewers** — external stakeholder / project contact tied to Medella Springs, not internal Alleato project staff\n- **Gordon Chapman** — external contact tied to Browning Chapman\n- **Andrea McClaine** — external contact tied to Merritt Contracting\n- **Jason Kiser** — external contact tied to Grey Rock Construction\n- **Katie Conner** — external contact on payment/proof-of-funds thread\n\nPoint of view: **Andrew is the clearest day-to-day Alleato operator on Westfield, and Brandon is involved when money/payment pressure shows up.** The rest of the internal team is not reliably surfaced because the directory tool failed.\n\nIf you want, I can take a second pass and build the team manually from:\n1. project directory records,\n2. meeting attendees,\n3. email traffic,\nso you get a practical org chart even if the formal directory data is messy."
